playlist.title: Cloudchord - Imprint
playlist.description:
Stream and DL: https://fanlink.to/cloudchord-imprint
"Imprint”, the first full length offering from guitarist/producer Derek VanScoten produced under his alias Cloudchord, drops March 21st on Gravitas Recordings. Drawing from obvious jazz and funk roots, the 12 track LP invites subtle influences of future bass, tropical house, and disco to mingle fluidly. However, it’s quickly discernible upon first listen that these influences have cemented into something new; the album is delivered as agreeably familiar yet blissfully fresh, mixing straight beat and broken rhythms with live guitar and poignant synth melodies throughout. Fans of live electronic and indie music will feel at home during the flavorful collaborations with SunSquabi of All Good Records and Los Angeles based trumpet player Erinn Bone.

tracks.title: Cloudchord - Seven Sisters (feat. Erinn Bone)
tracks.description:
Today I dropped a new song called “Seven Sisters.” 
It’s a guitar-meets-trumpet chill out track, and the first single off my upcoming album “Imprint,” out on March 21st.

Pre-Order Album Here: music.gravitasrecordings.com/album/imprint

The album is a feel good tropical-meets-future-bass affair, mixing straight beat and broken rhythms with live guitars. Each of the 12 songs symbolize a significant moment or phase of life. “Seven Sisters” represents family and community. 

I’ll be back next week with the second single.

This Album is a “Pay As You Want” release with all proceeds going directly to MAPS research.

http://www.maps.org/

MAPS mission :

Developing psychedelics and marijuana into prescription medicines

Training therapists and working to establish a network of treatment centers

Supporting scientific research into spirituality, creativity, and neuroscience

Educating the public honestly about the risks and benefits of psychedelics and marijuana.

We envision a world where psychedelics and marijuana are safely and legally available for beneficial uses, and where research is governed by rigorous scientific evaluation of their risks and benefits.

playlist.title: SugarBeats - Fly High LP
playlist.description:
FREE DOWNLOAD: bit.ly/shighfree
BANDCAMP: bit.ly/fhighbcamp
iTUNES: bit.ly/fhighitunes
BEATPORT: bit.ly/fhighbpt
SPOTIFY: bit.ly/fhighspfy

---------------------------------
Westwood is proud to welcome SugarBeats to the Westwood Recordings family with their debut full-length offering, the “Fly High” LP.
The Oregon-based duo has been bringing the funk up and down the west coast for over 5 years now, playing major festivals such as Lightning in a Bottle, What The Festival, and Burning Man. Garnering steady support from the Future Funk community and most recently winning 1st place in our Shambhala Remix Competition for the legendary producer Opiuo, we've had our eyes on the duo ever since as they've been building momentum towards their much anticipated debut album, "Fly High." The album features all original compositions recorded over the past year with a diverse cast of talented musicians and vocalists. Inspired by the sounds of funk, hip-hop, glitch, and future bass, SugarBeats have truly managed to uncover a sound of their own.

playlist.title: Lettuce - 'CRUSH'
playlist.description:
Pre-Order 'CRUSH' w/ exclusive bundles via: http://bit.ly/crushbundles 
Lettuce Tour-Dates: http://lettucefunk.com/tour
View the trailer for the upcoming documentary 
"LET US PLAY" https://youtu.be/bBjDtjd_qVw

"We made 'crush' in order to dispel the notion that a small group could wield infinite authority over the masses. With music, through unity and love, we will destroy any false sense of inferiority and remind us all that together we are the power." - Jesus Coomes

"CRUSH takes off where RAGE and FLY left off. We continue our journey of the Funk universe playing through many styles, including Psychedelia, Classic Soul, and Hip Hop. While still paying tribute to the past, this album clearly is pushing boundaries and has us heading into the Future.” - Adam “Shmeeans” Smirnoff

"Our vibe going into the studio for this record couldn't have been better. We played more shows than we ever had before leading up to the recording and I feel like we really captured that energy this time." - Ryan Zoidis

playlist.title: Rhythm Code II
playlist.description:
It is our collective pleasure to share with you the second Rhythm Code installment: another collection of the finest and most cutting edge psychedelic-squelch-bass-music to be found in the immediate galactic vicinity.. Enjoy the release in its flowing entirety, and help sustain the collective that is Shanti Planti, by downloading @ https://shantiplanti.bandcamp.com/album/rhythm-code-ii


"Daring to probe the depths of the mind and soul to peer into the underlying currents of our physical being is the Rhythm Code. A sonic exploration of the slick, ephemeral and surreal, this intricate array of outlandish sounds and primordial beats is a portal into the abysmal tides and archetypal lands that lie beneath the collective experience we dub reality. 

This revelatory collection from Shanti Planti draws together thirteen visionary minds from the healing realm of mid-tempo psychedelic electronica and follows them on their latest journey into the sensory fields that lie beyond the veil. 

Stretching across the vibrant landscapes of organic bass, cavernous glitch and psychedelic dub, this holographic world of drippy and curative sounds will evoke a new emotional experience for every listener while illuminating the shadows of uncharted imagination." - Christian Cortes, lostinsound.org 

Mastering by Preference Mastering

Released November 1, 2015

It is our collective pleasure to share with you the second Rhythm Code installment: another collection of the finest and most cutting edge psychedelic-squelch-bass-music to be found in the immediate galactic vicinity.. Enjoy the release in its flowing entirety, and help sustain the collective that is Shanti Planti, by downloading @ https://shantiplanti.bandcamp.com/album/rhythm-code-ii


"Daring to probe the depths of the mind and soul to peer into the underlying currents of our physical being is the Rhythm Code. A sonic exploration of the slick, ephemeral and surreal, this intricate array of outlandish sounds and primordial beats is a portal into the abysmal tides and archetypal lands that lie beneath the collective experience we dub reality. 

This revelatory collection from Shanti Planti draws together thirteen visionary minds from the healing realm of mid-tempo psychedelic electronica and follows them on their latest journey into the sensory fields that lie beyond the veil. 

Stretching across the vibrant landscapes of organic bass, cavernous glitch and psychedelic dub, this holographic world of drippy and curative sounds will evoke a new emotional experience for every listener while illuminating the shadows of uncharted imagination." - Christian Cortes, lostinsound.org

tracks.title: Whitebear x Tribone - Sensory Overload
tracks.description:
Collab with @tribone29

Free of stylistic constraints and immaculately produced, Whitebear’s aptly titled “Liberation”, is a bold statement in artistic freedom and originality. Having drawn inspiration from far and wide across the psychedelic stylistic spectrum, 'Liberation' speaks of a deeply transmutational journey, woven symbolically through intricately spacial sound design and dynamically entrancing grooves. 

Whitebear's third EP is an immense listening experience, taking the individual on a voyage to the very edge of their existence. A journey of self-actualisation, channelled and transmitted through sonic waves of aural ecstasy, each musical offering taking you deeper through the passage of change. With his signature blend of mid-tempo psychedelia, ancestral percussion, and growling vibrations that permeate your soul, Whitebear is about to take you on an intense journey into the very heart of your being. Prepare for the unexpected and almost ineffable experience that is 'Liberation'- this is Whitebear at the cutting edge of auditory evolution.

tracks.title: View Of Laniakea (Kaminanda Remix)
tracks.description:
Available through Bandcamp: https://desertdwellersmusic.bandcamp.com/album/the-great-mystery-remixes-part-1

Read the review from @theuntz: http://www.theuntz.com/news/liquid-stranger-leads-off-desert-dwellers-the-great-mystery-remixes-v1/

Earlier this year Desert Dwellers released their most diverse album in the duo's long career. The Great Mystery was the first full length collaborative project between the main founders Amani Friend and Treavor Moontribe, and featured a wide range of styles and aesthetics from downtempo and psychedelic dub to tribal trance to exotic house and techno flavors.

To celebrate the special release, Desert Dwellers have curated an ambitious two-part remix album full of contributions from some of the brightest luminaries and rising talents across the underground electronic music landscape. The Great Mystery Remixes Part 1 is slated for a September 21st release, and features sonic reinterpretations from Gaudi, Liquid Stranger, Hibernation, An-ten-nae, Kaminanda, AtYya, Tribone, Twin Shape, Land Switcher, Drumspyder, and Govinda. The second part will be released in late October with contributions from Emancipator, Whitebear, Sixis, Mystral, Supersillyus, Halfred, Master Minded, and many others. With artists from across the globe and musical genres, these carefully crafting renditions of Desert Dwellers' The Great Mystery are a potent combination of immersive soundscapes that pay a loving tribute to the original compositions.

https://desertdwellersmusic.bandcamp.com/album/the-great-mystery-remixes-part-1

The Great Mystery Remixes Part 2 ::: https://desertdwellersmusic.bandcamp.com/album/the-great-mystery-remixes-part-2 

Earlier this year Desert Dwellers released their most diverse album in the duo's long career. The Great Mystery was the first full length collaborative project just between the main founders Amani Friend and Treavor Moontribe, and featured a wide range of styles and aesthetics from downtempo and psychedelic dub to tribal trance to exotic house and techno flavors.

To celebrate the special release, Desert Dwellers have curated an ambitious two-part remix album with a total of 25 contributions from some of the brightest luminaries and rising talents across the underground electronic music landscape. The Great Mystery Remixes Part 2 is slated for a November 1st release on the DD Bandcamp page, and features sonic reinterpretations from Emancipator, Aligning Minds, Mumukshu, Sixis, David Starfire, Whitebear, Erothyme, Mystral, Master Minded, Halfred & Enzalla, Lulacruza, Bumble, Soohan, and Supersyllius. With artists from across the globe and musical genres, these carefully crafting renditions of Desert Dwellers' The Great Mystery are a potent combination of immersive soundscapes that pay a loving tribute to the original compositions.

playlist.title: KarmasynK - Furple Punk EP
playlist.description:
● Available to buy here: Beatport » http://btprt.dj/1JxBq1w, Bandcamp » http://bit.ly/1HNrcaK, iTunes » http://apple.co/1OQmY4W, Addictech » http://bit.ly/1U8QMg3, Spotify » http://bit.ly/1L9tcPC

● Glitch Hop Community releases a 6-track EP named Furple Punk by the USA based music producer KarmasynK.
All tracks were composed with great precision and floods of brilliant edits, overwhelming growling bass lines with smacking drums, bringing forth sick vibrations yet full of heavy funk glitched all the way up that will definitely make you move. The EP includes 3 original mixes and also 3 banging remixes by 4bstr4ck3r, Filip Rasch and Memetech who ripped these tunes apart and put them back together with their own unique styles and twists.
Dye your hair furple and feel the punk!

● Artwork: Point Zero Productions

● Mastering: Shawn Hatfield

playlist.title: Seeds Of Mind
playlist.description:
"Seeds of Mind" is Welch producer Kris Thomas' second EP with Shanti Planti Records. Each track weaves an intricate circuitry of futuristic glitches, eastern strings and dreamy soulful vocals. The organic melodies and driving basslines in Eurythmy's creations set him apart in psychedelic midtempo bass music. 

This new EP showcases "Pixel Palace", the third track, which is a collaboration with Melbourne based artist Schtang and the second track, "Seeds of Mind" features heart moving vocals from the English rose, Megan Lowman.
credits

----------
Westwood is proud to present "Delights" - The new album from Canadian electronic producer, Defunk. With a constantly evolving taste for bass music, Delights pushes his sound into new territories as he combines his favorite elements of midtempo, glitch, and future bass music with old school funk, soul, and hiphop. The result is a sexy palette of funky rhythms, dirty drops, jazzy solos, and special guest appearances from featured vocalists and instrumentalists alike including the Ragga Twins, Sam Klass, Marshall McGee, the Raya Brass Band and more.

The result is a sexy palette of funky rhythms, dirty drops, jazzy solos, and special guest appearances from featured vocalists and instrumentalists alike including the Ragga Twins, Sam Klass, Marshall McGee, the Raya Brass Band and more.

In the last few years, Toronto based Bangladesh native Saad Ayub has stepped up to the plate with his signature sound and now turns to the Who’s Afraid Of 138?! imprint. tracks.title: Petrichord (Alex M.O.R.P.H. Remix) by Tyler Sherritt - TranceMusic.NET Premiere
tracks.description:
SUBSCRIBE: http://bit.ly/W47YrE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To be released on Garuda Music September 23rd, 2013!

As soon as we saw Alex M.O.R.P.H. attached to this massive release, we knew we were all in for a treat.  He's taken the track in his trademark big-room trance style, and why shouldn't he?  When it's done this well, it can cut through the crowd like a laser.  The breakdown is as epic as anything, and when the build comes, you're ready for the drop like never before.  A nice, uptempo feel will get even the most hard-hearted dancers moving, and it's clear that this remix is a true professional at work.

playlist.title: Dirtwire - RipTide LP
playlist.description:
Dirtwire's RipTide album is OUT NOW  through Beats Antique Records. Visit riptide.dirtwire.net for more info.

As the cycles of life, weather patterns, and geopolitical shifts whirl about them, Dirtwire, Available at: http://riptide.dirtwire.net

Bay-Area based electro acoustic duo of David Satori (Beats Antique) and Evan Fraser (Hamsa Lila, Stellamara), contain that energy in their latest release, RipTide, out now through Beats Antique Records. With tracks highlighting the duo’s unique blend of dirt and wire, the album expertly combines acoustic, electric and electronic elements, which are carefully chosen and mixed together into their musical alchemy with pride. The album follows recent appearances at Coachella and Lucidity festivals, and is followed by a Summer tour along the West Coast, as well as an appearance at Sonic Bloom in Colorado.

tracks.description:
Free Download: https://www.toneden.io/dirtwire/post/dirtwire-riptide-freddy-todd-remix

Celebrating the New Year with a special remix of RipTide from Freddy Todd. Grab the new track for free download, or name your price to get it, along with the entire RipTide release, on Bandcamp.

https://dirtwiremusic.bandcamp.com/track/riptide-freddy-todd-remix

We’re headed to Colorado next week for shows in Ft. Collins, Aspen, and in Denver with the Everyone Orchestra for Cervantes’ 14th Anniversary. After that, we will be in Costa Rica for Envision Festival and in Arizona for Gem and Jam! Visit dirtwire.net/event for the full list of dates.

Freddy is heading off for two shows in both Fargo and Bismark this weekend, then off to NYC in February and Detroit in March. Visit freddytodd.com to find a show near you.

1. PSYCHEDELIC BOOMBOX

tracks.title: Dreaming In Dub [Middle Peace Compilation - Shanti Planti]
tracks.description:
My contribution to the outstanding new compilation from Whitebear / Shanti Planti. All proceeds from this release are going to Save the Children, to help all the children who have had their lives ripped apart by the recent (and ongoing) atrocities in Gaza. Please go get the release, not only is it for a great cause, it is also STUFFED with amazing music..!!

From the bandcamp page:

No one knows when or where the next crisis will strike. But we do know that children are disproportionately affected in times of crisis- and often suffer most. In an age of armchair activism and Facebook shares, likes and temporary Facebook rage (usually expressed in a concise status friendly sentence), I've been called to action. 

It is with great pleasure that we announce the release of Shanti Planti's 2nd V/A Compilation titled "Middle Peace". Shanti Planti and the artists involved with this project have devoted much of their time and craft to create an incredible collection of conscious frequencies in a bid to raise funds to help the organization SaveTheChildren provide immediate emergency relief, healthcare, education and protection for children where necessary. STC creates Child-Friendly Spaces for children to safely play and learn, even in the midst of crisis. Unique among emergency responders, Save the Children stays as long as it takes after crisis strikes, helping children, families and communities recover from their losses and rebuild their lives. 

For this compilation we will be focusing on raising money for children and families in the Gaza Strip that have been ravaged by recent conflict. We plan on making this an annual affair and hope to build a strong partnership with the SavetheChildren Foundation. 

We are incredibly blessed, please help us help our less fortunate brothers and sisters. 

ALL PROCEEDS WILL GO TO SAVETHECHILDREN.
credits
released 29 October 2014 

All tracks produced by the artist unless otherwise specified. 

Artwork by Abzzolum 
www.facebook.com/pages/Abzzolum/168964616537942 

Mastering by Saxon Higgs/UProoted Mastering 
www.facebook.com/pages/UProoted-Mastering/327511057421844?fref=ts

tracks.title: Do Right
tracks.description:
Free download 

The song tells the narrative of a woman who is complaining about her partner's apparent financial insolvency. She states that he was financially well off in 1922, but now has nothing. She claims it is because he wasted it on other women, and that these lovers will no longer show any interest in him now that he is poor. She claims that he tricked her into a relationship where all he has to offer her is "a drink of gin." She ends each verse asking why the man does not 'do right' by her, and then throws him out, insisting that he go earn a living in order to support her.

tracks.title: K+lab - Wrecked feat Analog mc (Opiuo Remix)
K+lab, Stickybuds - Super Gravy ft Laughton Kora & Bailey Wiley
tracks.description:
Gramatik & Lowtemp present:

Super Gravy.

Official Music video here> https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=An83j85rZSc&feature=youtu.be

Two heavyweights of the glitch hop scene, K+Lab and Stickybuds, join forces for a funk-filled release on Gramatik’s independent label Lowtemp. Featuring guest vocals from Laughton Kora and Bailey Wiley, the track they’ve cooked up is hotter than a fistful of chilies. With its irresistible horn hooks, banging drums and heavy bass, “Super Gravy” is a summer anthem in the making and everything one would expect from two top notch producers at the top of their game.

playlist.title: Funkaholism EP (Free Download)
playlist.description:
Since it's almost christmas I thought it would be a nice gesture to give away an EP!
And it's now available for download!!!!!!

Here is the wav file EP link
https://beatfatigue.bandcamp.com/album/funkaholism-ep

And the mp3 EP link
https://www.facebook.com/pages/Beat-Fatigue/603641212989426?sk=app_220150904689418

I want everybody to be able to get this one!! AWESOME!
 
I also want to let you know that I really want to take my music production and my live performance to the next level. I got big plans and I want my next release to be as big as I currently have created in my mind. And therefore I need some serious new equipment, instruments and collaborations to be able to do this, so every little donation will be very much appreciated and used for quality new equipment to get better and more awesome results for my next release! Thanks in advance, you are all awesome!

Please enjoyy!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Cheeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeersssssssssssssssss

tracks.title: Hard To Believe (Funkaholism EP)
tracks.description:
Yooooo00oo00oo!!!!!!
Hope you are doing good!
So who's ready for a free EP?!?!

It suddenly hit me that I never dropped a free EP and I think there is no better time than now to give one before starting the new year! 
And since I am veryyy close to 8000 people that follow me on soundcloud now, I think it's a great time to show some gratitude to all you awesome peoplesss out theree with a free Funk EP!!!

This is the first track of the EP, I never 'sample' anything, so I thought why not try that out once for fun. Hope you enjoy this free dl!! 

it will be available for free to download on the 11th of December :).

And the awesome artwork is made by Cyberelg!
Check him out; https://www.facebook.com/Cyberelg !!

Chuuuuuuuuuuurss

playlist.title: Don't Forget To Bring A Towel EP
playlist.description:
This time Glitch Hop Community put out a fresh sounding 3-track EP by the Germany based young talented producer LxOx. All 3 tracks were composed with an advanced technique and a great sense for melodies. This EP is ranging from soulful funk influenced vibes to heavy electronica with tough bass lines all put together in a one of a kind style providing a really enjoyable and colorful experience for the listener. Don't forget to bring a towel because top quality glitch hop sound waves are flooding the shores on this one!

playlist.title: Malfunktionality Part One Album (Out Now!!!)
playlist.description:
Well the time has finally come! The preview of Beat Fatigue's debut album 'Malfunktionality is up on soundcloud!
'I had so much fun working on this, that I literally had no idea that it would turn out so great! This is the sound that I've been looking for for a long time now. An album was the only option I had, so many ideas were flowing through my mind that I had to put into one album!' 
The album is divided in two parts, the first part contains twelve bluesy jazzy dance floor funkers. The second part of the album is containing all the collaborations with amazing artists that will be released later this year.

Tracklist:
1. A Blues Malfunktion
2. Sowieso Good
3. Fat Iced Tea
4. Euforia Fatigue
5. Plectrum
6. Fragile Funk Cat
7. Fatigued Blues May Intrigue Kangaroos
8. Ratakatat
9. Tone Hormones
10. Feisty Frappucino 
11. One Flute Over The Cuckoo's Nest
12. Déjà Vu

Final Art Design By Clint Grierson
Label: Adapted Records
Release date: 9th Of June

playlist.title: CloZee - The Poetic Assassin (Out on Gravitas Recordings)
playlist.description:
I'm extremely excited to share with you this new project, and honored to release it on Gravitas Recordings.  

You can download it for FREE / PAY WHAT YOU WANT (we are always very grateful for any money that you can spare, however little) through Gravitas's Bandcamp : http://music.gravitasrecordings.com/album/the-poetic-assassin

Really hope you 'll like it guys. Please help us to spread it by sharing! :)

Thank you so so much to the awesome Gravitas Team, The Calm Project, Swal (Lulu Swallow), Adrien Giordana (for Lantern Dance's lyrics) and all of you guys for supporting my music for the past 2 years.

tracks.title: That's The Spot
tracks.description:
New Pantyraid Music - Get "Wanting Moves" HERE: http://smarturl.it/prafterglow

FIND A SHOW NEAR YOU ~ http://pantyraidmusic.com
-----------------------------------------
2.23 - Envision Festival - Costa Rica

The second single release in PANTyRAiD PillowTalk countdown, "That's the Spot" is a unique song - from the start it feels like you are immersed in a sexy rollercoaster ride. We wanted it to have moments of R&B tension, moments of  stomping steady beat, and moments of psychedelic intensity, all wrapped in the feel of a dancey entanglement of power and lust.

Visit http://pillowtalk.pantyraidmusic.com to preorder the album and get instant download of "That's the Spot," as well as some other free suprises of the pantydropping nature.

Or grab the stand-alone single from your favorite online retailer.

We love you and can't thank you enough for the support.

Say no to slavery ~ Worship the Sun

Ooah + MartyParty
